Q1 : git fetch vs git pull ? 

Sure 👍 here’s a short and simple explanation of what’s shown in the images:

🟠 Git Fetch - it cannot give merge conflict 

It downloads the latest changes from the remote repository into your local repository, but

It does NOT update your working files or current branch.

You can review the changes first, then merge manually when you’re ready.
✅ Safe to use anytime, no risk of overwriting your work.

