Q : What is virtual thread vs platform thread? 
Ans : 

Perfect question 👏 Let’s make it **super simple** 👇

---

### 🧩 **Platform Thread vs Virtual Thread**

| Feature              | **Platform Thread**                               | **Virtual Thread**                         |
| -------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| **What it is**       | Normal Java thread (traditional)                  | Lightweight thread (new in Java 19+)       |
| **Created by**       | Operating System (OS)                             | Java Virtual Machine (JVM)                 |
| **Memory usage**     | Heavy — each thread takes a lot of memory (~1 MB) | Very light — only a few KB per thread      |
| **How many can run** | Limited (few thousands max)                       | Can create thousands or even millions      |
| **Speed**            | Slower to create and switch                       | Very fast and scalable                     |
| **Best for**         | CPU-heavy tasks                                   | I/O-heavy tasks (like web calls, DB calls) |

---

### 💬 **In short:**

> 🧠 **Platform threads** = old, heavy, OS-managed threads.
> ⚡ **Virtual threads** = new, super-light Java-managed threads (Project Loom).

---

### 💡 **Simple Example:**

If your app needs to handle 10,000 users:

* Platform threads → ❌ Might run out of memory
* Virtual threads → ✅ Easily possible

---

### 🧠 Analogy:

> Platform thread = a full truck 🚛 (heavy, strong but few)
> Virtual thread = a scooter 🛵 (light, many can run together)

