Q: What is spring cloud ? 
Ans : 
“Spring Cloud” is a set of tools built on top of Spring Boot that helps you easily create microservices.

Simple meaning:

Spring Cloud gives ready-made features so your microservices can talk to each other, discover each other, handle
failures, and manage configuration — without you writing everything from scratch.

In layman terms:

Imagine you have many small apps (microservices).
Spring Cloud works like a manager that helps them:

Find each other (Service Discovery – Eureka)

Share common settings (Config Server)

Call each other safely (OpenFeign)

Handle failures (Circuit Breaker – Resilience4j)

Route requests properly (API Gateway) 


Q : what steps to follow for development of microservices? 
In microservice development… I normally follow a clear step-by-step approach. [pause]

First… I start with domain breakdown — I identify the business modules and split them into small independent 
services… like user service, booking service, payment service etc. [pause]

Second… I design clear REST APIs for each microservice… with proper request and response models. [pause]

Third… each microservice gets its own database… so that services stay loosely-coupled and scalable. [pause]

Fourth… I implement communication between services… normally using REST APIs or message broker like Kafka… to make
them async and reliable. [pause]

Fifth… I add centralized configuration, logging, and monitoring… using config server, ELK, Zipkin etc. [pause]

Finally… I use Docker + CI/CD for deploying each microservice independently… so we can scale and release features 
faster."

