### Q2: In code, where is the IoC Container present?

> The **IoC Container** is managed by Spring and is represented by the **ApplicationContext**. It is created automatically when the Spring Boot application starts.

```java
@SpringBootApplication
public class Application {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(Application.class, args);
    }
}
```

`SpringApplication.run()` starts the IoC Container. ✅

