### Q3: Where have you used `@Bean` in your project?

> I used `@Bean` for **ModelMapper**. I created a separate configuration class annotated with `@Configuration` and defined a method annotated with `@Bean` to create and manage the ModelMapper object as a Spring bean.

Example:

```java
@Configuration
public class AppConfig {

    @Bean
    public ModelMapper modelMapper() {
        return new ModelMapper();
    }
}
```

Then I inject it using `@Autowired` wherever required. ✅
                                           